Testing, testing, testing!!! Here are the letters for each grade level for testing this morning. Please text me if you are having issues and we will help you login 530-966-7748 (Mrs. Newman) or 209-658-2247 (Mrs. Freeman).

Before you call or text please watch this video :)!

https://youtu.be/GU-D78vZ4mw

If you get an error that the browser doesn't support the test... at the same time hit "Control" then "Shift" then the number "0"

https://www.wheatlandhigh.org/documents/School%20Reopening/2020-21%20Distance%20Learning%20Bell%20Schedule_website.pdf

Thanks so much for your patience!!!

Nicole Newman, Superintendent

post_text:
Good morning,

When we planned our July 24th graduation we were anticipating the curve to flatten and cases to decrease. This has not been the case. The District puts our students, staff, family‚Äôs, and communities health and safety first and we are not willing to bring nearly 1000 people into the stadium at this time given the current closures.

We will have the virtual graduation completed by the end of next week and will distribute to everyone! We are thankful that we had the graduation parade to celebrate our graduates! What a great tradition we have started!!!

I know this won‚Äôt be a happy message, but please know that it was not an easy decision. This has been an extremely difficult time for all of us! We appreciate your continued support.

Nicole Newman, Superintendent

post_text:
The Reopening Plan for 2020 DRAFT has been complete and is available for review.

Please feel free to send comments to nnewman@wheatlandhigh.org. The original plan (completed yesterday) had masks as optional, but the CDPH amended their original guidance and deleted the footnote that pertained to schools having masks recommended, but not required. In the event that they return to being recommended we will follow that guidance.

A reminder that we have 3 options for school (this information can be found on pages 12-13 of our plan. We are thankful that we have multiple programs to meet the needs of your students.

Also, clarification for the school day with the traditional schedule next year at WUHS... All students will have a 1st period and classes will begin at 8:15 for all students. We will have additional bus routes to avoid overcrowding.

Again, if you have any questions or want to give input on the plan please do not hesitate to contact me.

The plan will go to the Board on July 15, 2020.

Nicole Newman, Superintendent

https://www.wheatlandhigh.org/School-Reopening-/index.html

Nicole Newman, Superintendent

Attention 2020-2021 Fall Athletes:

It‚Äôs time to start working on your athletic clearance to play sports at WUHS. The 2020-2021 Athletic Clearance info sheet is pictured below and gives you all the info you need to complete the online clearance. Please make sure when you begin,to choose the 2020-2021 school year.
All students are required to have a current physical. WUHS will be having a physical night on July 29th at 6pm. If you need one sooner than that, please see the Sports Physical info picture. We have verified that these doctors are taking appts for sports physicals. Lastly, if you need the form to bring with you, I have attached a blank one. You can also find all three of these forms at www.wheatlandhigh.org under the athletics tab. If you have any questions or concerns, please contact Ms. Kat at kgriego@wheatlandhigh.org.

It is time to begin preparing for our Virtual Graduation Video!
Remember that this IS NOT a replacement for the in person graduation that we are hoping to have on July 24th.

We know that many of you still have not received your cap and gown. We have delivered the first round and have another round to deliver this week. If you have not ordered one you need to do so. Please contact Mrs. Embree at rembree@wheatlandhigh.org if you need assistance.

Please email your video to mhood@wheatlandhigh.org. Videos will be screened for appropriate content.

If you have a cap and gown please go ahead and submit your video. The drop dead date for videos to be turned in by is June 15th.

Criteria for Virtual Graduation

Please submit a 15 second video in your cap and gown that answers one of the following questions or something similar:

A thank you to your parents‚Ä¶
A thank you to your favorite teacher‚Ä¶
A favorite memory of your experience at WUHS/EPD...
Your hopes and dream/goals for the future...

Happy Friday! A big part of our school leadership is our Student Board Member position. Walker Lee has served in this capacity for the 2019-20 school year and will be leaving this summer and has accepted an offer to attend the United States Naval Academy in Annapolis.

It is now the time to select a new Student Board Member. If you are interested, please fill out the application and submit it to Nicole Newman, Superintendent at nnewman@wheatlandhigh.org.

Please feel free to reach out with any questions to Mrs. Newman or our Wheatland Union High School District Board President, Tony Lopez at tlopez@wheatlandhigh.org. Applications are due May 18, 2020.

Wheatland Union High School Track and Field
April 3 at 10:12 PM ¬∑

If you haven‚Äôt heard, CIF officially canceled the season. I really appreciated all of your hard work early on because I saw that you were destined for greatness. But at this point, we will never get that opportunity. I want to remind all of you that this chapter may be over but that doesn‚Äôt mean you stop building your great story. I want to thank our incredible 4 year seniors, Matthew Hahn-Atckinson and Christopher Soderlund for your incredible commitment to this program. You two leave this program having won two league championships and both will continue their track careers at the community college level. Thank again to all of you and stay safe. Until next year.

I want to thank our incredible 4 year seniors, Matthew Hahn-Atckinson and Christopher Soderlund for your incredible commitment to this program. You two leave this program having won two league championships and both will continue their track careers at the community college level. Thank again to all of you and stay safe. Until next year.

post_text:
Good Afternoon Pirate Family,

WUHSD will be following the approved board calendar and will be closed for Spring break the week of April 6 ‚Äì 13, 2020.

All online learning platforms will be available for students to access during Spring break, but there will no new, required work assigned.

We encourage students to resume working online on Monday, April 13th. Online learning will officially resume on Tuesday, April 14th.

There have also been a lot of questions about grading for the second semester especially since guidance was given yesterday from UC and CSUs. We have not made a decision yet about the direction we will go for grading. We have a leadership meeting tomorrow afternoon and will have a decision released no later than Monday, April 6.

Stay safe Pirates!

Nicole Newman, Superintendent
